## edge_agent/rel/vm.args.eex
## Customize flags given to the VM: http://erlang.org/doc/man/erl.html
## -mode/-name/-sname/-setcookie are configured via env vars, do not set them here

## =============================================================================
## Scheduler Configuration
## =============================================================================

## Number of dirty schedulers doing IO work (shell command execution via ports, SQLite file ops)
## Dirty IO schedulers do NOT handle gen_tcp socket I/O (SSH tunnels, proxy connections) —
## that goes through BEAM epoll/kqueue polling. Only System.cmd and file ops use these.
+SDio 4

## Number of dirty CPU schedulers for computationally intensive NIFs
## EdgeAgent: Minimal CPU-heavy work (mostly I/O)
+SDcpu 2

## Scheduler bind type - spread across CPU cores for better distribution
+sbt db

## Scheduler busy wait threshold (microseconds)
## Lower = more responsive for proxy and SSH connections
+sbwt very_short

## =============================================================================
## Network & Distribution
## =============================================================================

## Increase number of concurrent ports/sockets
## EdgeAgent: SSH tunnels, proxy connections, metrics collection
+Q 32768

## Distribution buffer busy limit (KB)
## EdgeAgent: Only connects to ONE admin (no peer-to-peer traffic)
## Keep default since no heavy inter-node traffic
+zdbbl 8192

## Kernel poll - use efficient epoll/kqueue for socket events
+K true

## Async thread pool size for legacy async file I/O operations
## Handles SQLite file ops and log files. Socket I/O goes through BEAM polling, not here.
+A 8

## =============================================================================
## Memory Management
## =============================================================================

## Heap memory strategy - initial heap size (words) before first GC
## Proxy forward loop processes are tiny. Large command output goes to binary heap (+hmbs).
## 4096 words pre-allocated per process is wasteful at high proxy concurrency.
+hms 1024

## Binary heap management - threshold for storing binaries off-heap
## EdgeAgent: Shell command output can be large
+hmbs 4096

## Maximum number of processes
## EdgeAgent: Each command execution spawns a Task, plus SSH sessions, proxy connections
## Default 262144 should be sufficient for typical agent workload
##+P 524288

## =============================================================================
## Distribution Port Configuration
## =============================================================================

## Agents are NOT Erlang distribution nodes.
## From design docs: "Agents have no Erlang cookie, no epmd, no Node.connect."
## Admin -> Agent communication is HTTP only (API token auth, VPN DNS name).
## The settings below are intentionally omitted — distribution is never started on agents.

## =============================================================================
## Garbage Collection
## =============================================================================

## Tweak GC to run more often (reduces memory spikes from large command outputs)
##-env ERL_FULLSWEEP_AFTER 10

## =============================================================================
## Telemetry & Debugging
## =============================================================================

## Enable kernel polling statistics (for runtime introspection)
+KP true

## Crash dump settings
-env ERL_CRASH_DUMP /tmp/erl_crash_<%= System.get_env("HOSTNAME") || "agent" %>.dump
-env ERL_CRASH_DUMP_SECONDS 30
